{"person":{"id":"X01911","has_descendants_documented":false,"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":true},"birth":{"year":1752,"month":7,"day":7,"city":"Norwalk","county":"Fairfield County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1805,"month":1,"day":1,"city":"Bridgeport","county":"Fairfield County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_research_notes":"Capt. John Cannon","mother_research_notes":"Esther Perry Cannon"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H01237","children_ids":["HD2793","HD2794","HD2795","HD2796","HD2797","HD2798","HD2799","HD2800"],"date_year":1777,"date_month":7,"location_city":"Norwalk","location_state":"Connecticut"}],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":["bridgeport_founder","physician","slaveholder"],"sources":[{"short":"St. John Genealogy"}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["civic_service"],"notable_blurb":"Bridgeport founder, physician, turnpike company founder"},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Co-founder of the Borough of Bridgeport","detail":"His estate was distributed in 1805 to his widow Sarah and their children. A note in the research suggests a John Cannon (possibly his son) founded the Bridgeport Bank in 1806 and served as its president from 1823 until 1827 — the probate timeline makes it likely this was the son John Jr. (HD2793) rather than the physician himself. In the 1790 US Census, one enslaved person was enumerated in his household. His daughter Antoinette married U.S. Senator Thaddeus Betts; his daughter Sarah married back into the St. John family. (St. John Genealogy; Bridgeport historical records)","body":"John Cannon Jr. moved from Norwalk to Bridgeport (then called Newfield) around 1790. He was involved in founding the Newfield Fire Company (1796), helped in